\chapter{Source Code}
\label{\detokenize{code:source-code}}\label{\detokenize{code:welcome-to-spiral-organiser-s-documentation}}\label{\detokenize{code::doc}}\label{\detokenize{code:module-spiralOrg}}\index{spiralOrg (module)}\index{dataclean() (in module spiralOrg)}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{code:spiralOrg.dataclean}}\pysiglinewithargsret{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{spiralOrg.}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{dataclean}}}{\emph{data}, \emph{features={[}{]}}}{}
Takes the dataset and the feature list to run SVM on with the class-label included.
generates a NxN numpy.ndarray depending upon the size of the dataset passed.

\end{fulllineitems}

\index{organise() (in module spiralOrg)}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{code:spiralOrg.organise}}\pysiglinewithargsret{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{spiralOrg.}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{organise}}}{\emph{data}, \emph{features={[}{]}}, \emph{threshold='stdev'}}{}
Spiral organiser. takes the dataset, feature list to run SVM on and the threshold value
threshold can be any of the following:
\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
mean

\item {} 
median

\item {} 
stdev (standard deviation)

\end{itemize}

Threshold refers to the threshold value with which we swap the rows.

\end{fulllineitems}
